76	Maybe you thought your mom would be there, helping with midnight feedings. Or your aunt would drop off a casserole, and your cousins would swing by to keep your kid entertained. But now? It’s just you, your partner, and the same four walls.\n\nIt’s totally okay to feel like you're doing this alone.\n\nBut guess what? You can build your own support system—even if it’s not the one you pictured. Here’s how:\n\n**Video calls with family:** Don’t wait for the big events. Even a quick 10-minute check-in with the fam can make you feel more connected and less lonely.\n\n**Voice messages & lullabies: **Ask your family back home to record stories or bedtime songs in your native language. Your kid will love hearing familiar voices, and it’ll make bedtime special.\n\n**Create a cultural memory box:** Gather photos, trinkets, and memories from your home country. It’s like creating a little visual time capsule that connects your child to their roots.\n\nIt might take a little time to create your village, but with a little effort, you'll have the support you need. You got this!\n\n	\N	2025-04-22 22:08:28.417	2025-04-22 22:08:30.892	2025-04-22 22:08:30.879	1	1	en	\N	f	0	0	0	Parenting Without a Village: How to Build Your Own Support System
