75	<p data-start="169" data-end="404" class="">Let’s be honest—some days feel like survival mode.<br data-start="219" data-end="222">\n</p><p data-start="169" data-end="404" class=""><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">You’ve got laundry on the couch, a clingy kid on your hip, and a mental checklist that just won’t quit.</span><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">If you’ve ever said, “I just need one </span><em data-start="366" data-end="372" style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">easy</em><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);"> win today,” this one’s for you.</span></p><p data-start="406" data-end="553" class="">The secret sauce? <strong data-start="424" data-end="437">Routines.</strong><br data-start="437" data-end="440">\n</p><p data-start="406" data-end="553" class="">Not military-style schedules.<br data-start="469" data-end="472">\nJust simple rhythms that bring structure without sucking the joy out of your day.</p><h3 data-start="560" data-end="593" class="">What Is a Routine, Really?</h3><p data-start="595" data-end="751" class="">It’s not about having a rigid timeline.<br data-start="634" data-end="637">\nIt’s about having <strong data-start="655" data-end="678">predictable rhythms</strong> that help your child feel secure—and help you breathe a little easier.</p><p data-start="753" data-end="761" class="">Think:</p><ul><li><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">Morning flow: Wake → Dress → Eat → Brush</span><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);"><br></span></li><li><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">Evening rhythm: Dinner → Bath → Book → Bed</span></li></ul><p data-start="855" data-end="975" class="">Kids thrive when they know what comes next.<br data-start="898" data-end="901">\nAnd bonus? You stop answering “What are we doing now?” for the 400th time.</p><h3 data-start="982" data-end="1016" class="">Start With Anchor Moments</h3><p data-start="1017" data-end="1114" class="">Anchor routines are things that <strong data-start="1049" data-end="1063">don’t move</strong>, no matter how wild the day gets.<br data-start="1097" data-end="1100">\nFor example:</p><ul><li><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">Breakfast always comes after brushing teeth</span><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);"><br></span></li><li><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">Bedtime always starts with a bath and story</span><span style="font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); background-color: var(--bs-card-bg);"><br></span></li></ul><p data-start="1017" data-end="1114" class=""><span style="font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); background-color: var(--bs-card-bg);">These act like </span><em data-start="1226" data-end="1246" style="font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); background-color: var(--bs-card-bg);">little lighthouses</em><span style="font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); background-color: var(--bs-card-bg);"> for your kid (and for your brain).</span></p><p data-start="1017" data-end="1114" class=""><img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," data-filename="anchor_routines_are_things_that_don_t_move.jpeg" style="width: 794.667px;"><span style="font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); background-color: var(--bs-card-bg);"><br></span></p><h3 data-start="1288" data-end="1337" class="">Keep It Realistic (Not Pinterest-Perfect)</h3><p data-start="1338" data-end="1533" class="">No one’s routine looks like a parenting ad.<br data-start="1381" data-end="1384">\nSome days, storytime lasts 20 minutes. Other days, it’s “here’s a hug and goodnight.”<br data-start="1469" data-end="1472">\nThat’s okay.<br data-start="1484" data-end="1487">\nThe goal is <strong data-start="1499" data-end="1530">consistency over perfection</strong>.</p><p data-start="1535" data-end="1621" class="">Start with just <strong data-start="1551" data-end="1566">one routine</strong> that could use help—like bedtime—and build from there.</p><h3 data-start="1628" data-end="1658" class="">Get the Kids Involved</h3><p data-start="1659" data-end="1742" class="">Routines feel way less like rules when your child helps build them.<br data-start="1726" data-end="1729">\nTry saying:</p><ul><li><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">“What should we do after snack time—read or play outside?”</span><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);"><br></span></li><li><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">“Should we brush teeth before or after our story tonight?”</span></li></ul><p data-start="1870" data-end="1947" class="">Giving them choice makes them more likely to <strong data-start="1915" data-end="1946">cooperate instead of resist</strong>.</p><h3 data-start="1954" data-end="1981" class="">Add Little Rituals</h3><p data-start="1982" data-end="2037" class="">Want routines to stick? Make them a little <em data-start="2025" data-end="2034">special</em>.</p><ul><li><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">A silly dance while brushing teeth</span><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);"><br></span></li><li><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">A “3 things you’re grateful for” moment before bed</span><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);"><br></span></li><li><span style="background-color: var(--bs-card-bg); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">A secret handshake to start the morning</span></li></ul><p data-start="2177" data-end="2228" class="">These small touches turn “tasks” into <strong data-start="2215" data-end="2227">memories</strong>.</p><p data-start="2258" data-end="2459" class="">Routines aren’t about being strict.They’re about creating <strong data-start="2319" data-end="2340">calm in the chaos</strong>.<br data-start="2341" data-end="2344">\nThey give you fewer things to think about—and give your child more space to feel secure, confident, and in control.</p><p data-start="211" data-end="426" class="">\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</p><p data-start="2461" data-end="2576" class="">And on those messy, meltdown-filled days?<br data-start="2502" data-end="2505">\nThat little bit of structure might be the thing that saves your sanity.</p>	t	2025-04-09 20:48:08.591	2025-04-09 21:07:40.133	2025-04-09 20:48:08.577	\N	\N	en	2025-04-09 20:52:10.318	f	0	0	1	Parenting Without Overwhelm: Routines That Actually Work
